Now let me think about this more carefully. Let me look at how `url.join(path)` works with paths containing spaces. The `url` crate's `join` method will percent-encode spaces in path segments. So a relative path like `group=foo bar/part-0001.parquet` would be joined to the table root and become something like `memory:///table/group=foo%20bar/part-0001.parquet`.

