Now I see clearly: the `path` in `ScanFile` comes from `getters[0].get_opt(row_index, "scanFile.path")` - this is the path from the Delta log which is percent-encoded.

Now let me trace back to the key issue. Let me look at how `file_url` (the URL used as the file_id value) is constructed in `visit_scan_file` (in the delta-rs crate, not kernel):

```rust
fn visit_scan_file(ctx: &mut ScanContext, scan_file: ScanFile) {
    let file_url = match ctx.parse_path(&scan_file.path) {
        ...
    };
}
```

And `parse_path` does:
```rust
fn parse_path(url: &Url, path: &str) -> DeltaResult<Url, DataFusionError> {
    Ok(match Url::parse(path) {
        Ok(url) => url,
        Err(_) => url.join(path).map_err(...)?,
    })
}
```

The `scan_file.path` is the percent-encoded path from the Delta log. So when partitioned by `group=foo%20bar`, the path would be `group=foo%20bar/part-0001.parquet`.

When `url.join("group=foo%20bar/part-0001.parquet")` is called, the `url` crate will treat `%20` as already-encoded, so it stays as `%20`. The resulting URL would be `memory:///table/group=foo%20bar/part-0001.parquet`. This is the `file_url` that gets used as the file_id value.

